text:
Set in the 1990s, Captain Marvel follows Danvers, an Air Force officer, as she becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after earth gets involved in a galactic war between alien. The film is directed by Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck, and it stars Brie Larson as Carol Danvers / Captain Marvel, alongside Samuel L. Jackson, Ben Mendelsohn, Djimon Hounsou, Lee Pace, Lashana Lynch, Gemma Chan, Annette Bening, Clark Gregg, and Jude Law.

Captain Marvel was released in theaters on March 8, 2019, and received generally positive reviews from critics, with many praising Larson's performance, the visual effects, and the action sequences. It grossed over $1.1 billion worldwide, making it one of the highest-grossing films of 2019.

In this film, we see Nick Fury (Samuel L. Jackson) as a younger man, still learning about the existence of superheroes and aliens. We also get to see how he loses his eye, which has been a mystery for years.

Captain Marvel is set before the events of Iron Man (2008), but its post-credits scene takes place after the events of Avengers: Infinity War (2018).

**Avengers: Endgame**

The culmination of 22 movies and 11 years of the Marvel Cinematic Universe, Avengers: Endgame is a superhero epic that brings together some of Marvel's mightiest heroes to save the world from Thanos' devastating snap.
